LAGOS – Corps members of the 2021 Batch ‘A’ stream 1 have been charged to keep the flag up as worthy ambassadors of the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC). This charge was made by the State Coordinator of NYSC Lagos, Mr. Eddy Megwa while briefing the corps members on the procedure for their passing out parade ceremony. According to Megwa, the ceremony which comes up on Thursday, 17th February 2022 at the Orientation camp Iyana-Ipaja by 10:00 am, will be presided over by Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu of Lagos State. Group Endorses NYSC Trust Fund Bill, Hails Reps Nunayon Apata Emerges Lagos ATPN Chairman The Lagos NYSC boss also used the medium to congratulate and thank all passing out corps members for exhibiting good behaviour during their service year even as he wished them success in their future endeavours. In a release signed by Mrs. Joyce Madaki, an Assistant Director, Press and Public Relations, NYSC, Lagos State, Megwa also imployed employers and the good people of Lagos State to accord the passing-out corps members every necessary assistance as they round off their service in the state. 